---
/**
 * TaxNotice — single source of truth for the "informational, not a filing" framing.
 *
 * SusuFinance is a record-keeping and analysis tool, not a tax-preparation service.
 * It produces jurisdiction-neutral records (what you own, what it cost, what you
 * realized) — never a filing document. Reused across every tax/year-end view so
 * the legal wording lives in exactly one place.
 */
---
<div class="tax-notice" role="note">
  <strong class="tax-notice__lead">Informational only — not a tax filing.</strong>
  <span>
    SusuFinance organizes your records and computes gains and losses from the data you've imported.
    It is not a filing document or tax advice, and tax rules vary by country. How you file is between
    you and your tax professional.
  </span>
</div>

<style>
  .tax-notice {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.3rem;
    background: var(--accent-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--accent-glow);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 0.85rem 1.1rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .tax-notice__lead {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
</style>
